    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/237">Heinricus</persName> divina favente clemencia
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Quia nullus extra
                        ecclesiam salvus potest fieri, consequens est, ut unusquisque fidelis
                        laborans in agro dei sine intermissione incumbat incremento ecclesiastice
                        rei. Certum est enim, quia, sicut exaltatur mater omnium vivencium, ita
                        crescit merces omnium sibi serviencium. Quapropter universorum eiusdem
                        fidelium tam presencium quam futurorum noverit caritas, quod nos
                        ecclesiasticis profectibus incumbentes ac dilectissime nostre coniugis <rs
                            key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> seu carissimi nostri filii regis
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/77">Heinrici</persName>
                        precibus pietatis aures accomodantes per presentis precepti stabile
                        firmamentum sancte <orgName key="#Mother_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/81">Vercellensi <rs key="#Mother_churches"
                                >ecclesie</rs></orgName>
                        <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">confirmamus</rs> omnia bona quiete tenenda
                        ac pacifice in eternum fruenda, que sancto Eusebio olim collata sunt a
                        nostris predecessoribus regibus vel imperatoribus seu quibuscumque
                        fidelibus. Sed ut mentes fidelium plenius gaudeant et predones caucius se
                        custodiant, <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            ref="#estates/131">Vercellensem <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs>
                        </geogName>et <geogName ref="#estates/132"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Comitatus #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Districtio"
                            >sancte Agathe </geogName>cum <rs key="#Districtio">districto</rs> et
                            <rs key="#Teloneum">theloneo</rs> et universa <rs>publica funccione
                        </rs>vel <rs key="#Public_exactions">exaccione</rs> aut redibicione confirmamus
                        Eusebiane ecclesie; <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/50">Buiellam</placeName> insuper cum omni sua integritate,
                        id est <placeName ref="#places/591"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Vernade</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/212"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Clauaza</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/457"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Bedollium</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/206"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Gallianicum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/208"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Ponderianam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/518"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Mulinariam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/210"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Andurnum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/211"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cisidulam</placeName>, corticellam in monte, <placeName ref="#places/3"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Carixianam</placeName> cum omni sua integritate, <placeName
                            ref="#places/51"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sextegnum</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/96"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rouisindam</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/517"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montem Uictimali,</placeName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/515"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pedrorium</placeName>; <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> quoque <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/274">Vercellensis</geogName> civitatis cum omnibus ad eam
                        pertinentibus, curticellam in <placeName ref="#places/227"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Audenic[o]</placeName>, curtem <geogName ref="#estates/129"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Canauam</geogName>, curtem <geogName ref="#estates/275"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Caualli</geogName>, <rs
                            key="#Monasteries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >abbaciam</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/107"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            >sancti Michahelis de <placeName ref="#places/328"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Laucedio</placeName>,</orgName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/99"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Firminianam</placeName>; curtem regiam quam <geogName
                            ref="#estates/273"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Orcum</geogName> nominant cum tota <geogName><rs
                                key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >silva</rs> walda</geogName> et <placeName ref="#places/49"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Fulgitio</placeName> et cum omnibus curtibus et villis, cum <placeName
                            ref="#places/103"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >valle Cliui;</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bridges/pontoons">pontem</rs> etiam <placeName
                            key="#Bridges/pontoons">Notingum</placeName>, quem <persName
                            ref="#people/109" key="#Bishops">Notingus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> eiusdem Vercellensis ecclesie mirabiliter
                        super eum equitando legaliter recepit; <placeName ref="#places/100"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            > >Languscum</placeName>, curtem de <geogName ref="#estates/98"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >><placeName ref="#places/105"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Aucimiano</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus suis pertinentiis,
                        aquam de<placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            ref="#places/611"> Scicida</placeName>, aquam de <placeName
                            ref="#places/613"
                            key="#Rivers #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            >Saruo</placeName>, aquam de <placeName ref="#places/614"
                            key="#Rivers #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            >Heleuo</placeName> cum utrisque <rs>ripis</rs> a loco ubi nascuntur
                        usque in Padum, aquam <placeName key="#Rivers">Padi</placeName> cum utrisque
                        ripis a <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/615">Lionna</placeName> usque
                        ad <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/240"><placeName
                                key="#Plebs" ref="#places/616">plebem Martori,
                            </placeName></orgName>aquam de <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            >Duria</placeName> cum utrisque ripis a <placeName ref="#places/617"
                            key="#Rivers">Petra grossa</placeName> usque in Padum, <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            ref="#places/221">Consade</placeName>, <placeName>Matascum</placeName>,
                            <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            ref="#places/213">Candele</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            ref="#places/215">Treuere</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            ref="#places/214">Cleuoli</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            >Sulza</placeName> cum <rs key="#Forests">silva</rs> Salsa, <rs
                            key="#Castle">castellum</rs>
                        <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            ref="#places/450">Quirini</placeName>, curtem <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Rivers #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Mills #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Markets #Public_exactions #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Slave"
                            ref="#estates/128">Torcelli</geogName> -- hec omnia [sancta
                        Ver]cellensis e[cclesia] <rs>proprio iure </rs>in eternum habeat cum omnibus
                        publicis <rs key="#Districtio">districtis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Markets #Periodic_markets">mercatis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Teloneum">theloneis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Fisheries">piscacionibus</rs>
                        <rs>venacionibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Ports">portibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> montibus et vallibus alpibus <rs
                            key="#Houses">edificiis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Slave">mancipiis</rs> utriusque sexus agris vineis capellis
                            <rs>pratis</rs>
                        <rs>pascuis</rs> silvis <rs key="#Rivers">aquis</rs> aquarumque decursibus
                            <rs>cultis et incultis.</rs> Et insuper speciali edicto sanccimus, ut in
                        omnibus supra nominatis locis nullus mortalium mercatum presumat instituere
                        aut districtum vel theloneum aut <rs key="#Fodrum">fodrum</rs> seu aliquam
                        publicam funccionem ac redibicionem exigere neque piscacionem aut venacionem
                        exercere, nisi ad profectum vel ad proprium ius ipsius ecclesie. Quicumque
                        ergo huic nostre confirmacioni contraierit, nostre maiestatis reus erit,
                        insuper mille libras auri se compositurum noverit, medietatem imperiali
                        camere et medietatem ecclesie, cui molestiam intulerit. Quod ut firmius
                        habeatur et diligencius ab omnibus observetur, hoc preceptum ex nostra
                        iussione factum nostris manibus subter confirmavimus ac sigilli nostri
                        impressione inferius insigniri iussimus et <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/366">Gregorio</persName> nostro fidelissimo deo dispensante
                        episcopo sancti Eusebii vicario ad perpetuam pacem sue ecclesie conservandum
                        contulimus. Signum domni Heinrici tercii regis invictissimi (M.) imperatoris
                        autem secundi. (SMP.) </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
